    weatherSealSpec: `St. Louis weather-seal specifications: EPDM rubber bottom seal withstands Missouri freeze-thaw cycling across 60 annual frost days. Standard vinyl seals fail within 3-5 years in St. Louis climate. Top and side astragal seals require silicone or EPDM compound rated for sustained sub-10F ambient. MoDOT winter salt-spray along Hampton, Kingshighway, and Lindbergh corridors corrodes hardware within 5-7 years on uncoated galvanized steel. Seal replacement typically runs $130-$280 per door.`,
