    weatherSealSpec: `Orlando weather-seal specifications: EPDM rubber bottom seal withstands subtropical humidity and UV exposure. Top and side astragal seals require UV-stabilized silicone or EPDM compound. Orlando does not face salt-spray corrosion like coastal Florida metros but humidity-driven biological growth on rubber seals requires semi-annual cleaning. FPA-certified door installations require specific compression-rated weather-seal systems. Seal replacement typically runs $130-$270 per door.`,
    springAndCable: `Orlando spring and cable systems: torsion-spring systems dominate modern Orlando CBS (concrete block and stucco) residential construction. Extension-spring systems are rare in post-2000 Florida construction. Galvanized cables are standard; Orlando's inland location avoids the salt-corrosion cable failures common in coastal Florida metros. Spring life runs 10,000-20,000 cycles on standard torsion. Vacation-rental properties with 3-5x typical residential duty cycles should specify high-cycle 30,000 torsion systems to avoid mid-season failures during tourist peaks.`,
