    springAndCable: `Sacramento spring and cable systems: torsion-spring systems dominate modern Sacramento tract construction from Elk Grove through Roseville. Extension-spring systems appear on older 1950s-1970s South Sacramento and Oak Park housing. Galvanized cables are standard. Spring life runs 10,000-20,000 cycles on standard torsion. Sacramento's extreme summer heat accelerates spring-steel fatigue; heat-rated spring compounds extend service life 15-20% over standard. High-cycle 30,000 torsion systems on East Sacramento active-use properties add $150-$300.`,
