    springAndCable: `Pittsburgh spring and cable systems: torsion-spring systems dominate modern Pittsburgh single-family and suburban construction. Extension-spring systems appear on older 1890s-1930s rowhouse tuck-under garages. Galvanized cables standard; stainless-steel cables on Fox Chapel and Sewickley Heights installations. Pittsburgh's steep-hillside tuck-under garages often have non-standard spring configurations requiring specialty expertise because track geometry follows the hillside grade. High-cycle 30,000 torsion systems on active-use Shadyside properties add $150-$300.`,
